com.gensym.util
Class Symbol

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.gensym.util.Symbol
public class Symbol
extends Object
implements Serializable

A class used for interning Strings as "symbols". Symbols have the following property: 

Symbol.intern (String s1).equals (Symbol.intern (String s2))
iff 
s1.equals (s2)

Symbols should typically be interned in static initialization code.

See Also:
String, Serialized Form

initialize

public static void initialize(int hashsize)
                       throws AlreadyInitializedException
Initializes the Hashtable used to keep symbols. If this is not called before a symbol is interned, the table is initialized to with the default size. NOTE: This method should only be called from within a "main" method.
Parameters:
hashsize - the size of the intern table
Throws:
AlreadyInitializedException - if the Hashtable has already been sized.

Initializes the hashtable used to keep symbols. If this is not called before a symbol is interned, the table is initialized to with the default size. NOTE: This method should only be called from within a "main" method.
Parameters:

size

public static int size()
Returns the number of interned symbols. Can be used during development to determine what arguments to use for initialize().

intern

public static Symbol intern(String symval)
Interns a symbol and returns it. Symbol text should be uppercase. By convention, variable names should be uppercased and end with an underscore. For example,
Symbol A_HANDY_SYMBOL_ = Symbol.intern("A-HANDY-SYMBOL");
Parameters:
symval - a string that is interned as a symbol
Returns:
the interned symbol

getPrintValue()

getPrintValue

public String getPrintValue()
Returns the String that was interned for the Symbol. The return value has the property that:

 (Symbol.intern (mySymbol.getPrintValue ()).equals (mySymbol))
will be true. This property is not shared by the String returned from Symbol.toString ().
Returns:
the String value of the Symbol
